<dl id="n08039i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08039i">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08039i"> 39(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> in fear of his life</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>De Valera&apos;s Envoy / Mr. Art O&apos;Brien&apos;s Claim for Loss of Documents / The Holyhead Incident</b> The case in which Mr. Art O&apos;Brien claims over &pound;6,000 from the British Government for wrongful arrest and internment, was resumed before the Irish Deportees&apos; Compensation Tribunal in London yesterday morning.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Miss O&apos;Brien, the claimant&apos;s sister, giving evidence said her mother who was over 70 years of age was lying ill in the flat at the time of the arrest, and she was so upset by the proceedings that witness <mark>feared for her life</mark>. <small> <a name="II13feb23" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#II13feb23"><cite title="source">Irish Independent</cite></a> (13 February 1923) 6/5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
